      {
        "id": 2158524,
        "name": "Gerhard P.  (P r @ \u20ac s e n t)",
        "username": "Gerhard_P",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-04T20:44:06.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It might have been that the WINE was modest \u2026 but the origin (NSG LSG) is certainly not modest - and it should have performed well above avarage \u2026</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Paul Savage\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Paul Savage:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It looks like Aegerter bottled the wine, but did not make the wine\u2026  i.e. vinify it.  Maybe that was Claude Peyes (spelling?).  I have not seen either name here in the States\u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Claude Poyes was the (late) donator of the vineyard to the Hospice de Nuits, Aegeter (I assume) did purchase the barrel, elevate and bottle it \u2026<br>\nThe 2-3 bottles of Aegeter I had (negociant and domaine) were just that \u2026 ok, but not exciting \u2026</p>\n<p>However, the vintage (1993) has not yet excited me generally \u2026 rarely any wine did really \u201csing\u201d so far (yes, there were 2-3 wines) \u2026  from Village to Grand cru \u2026 usually a bit \u201cangular\u201d, tannins a bit \u201cdry\u201d, not really sweet and round \u2026</p>\n<p>(all very general)</p>",
