      {
        "id": 2159120,
        "name": "Gerhard P.  (P r @ \u20ac s e n t)",
        "username": "Gerhard_P",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/8baadc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-04-05T17:39:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Claus Jeppesen\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Claus Jeppesen:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Gerhard P.\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Gerhard P.:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It might have been that the WINE was modest \u2026 but the origin (NSG LSG) is certainly not modest - and it should have performed well above avarage \u2026</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Paul Savage\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Paul Savage:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It looks like Aegerter bottled the wine, but did not make the wine\u2026  i.e. vinify it.  Maybe that was Claude Peyes (spelling?).  I have not seen either name here in the States\u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Claude Poyes was the (late) donator of the vineyard to the Hospice de Nuits, Aegeter (I assume) did purchase the barrel, elevate and bottle it \u2026<br>\nThe 2-3 bottles of Aegeter I had (negociant and domaine) were just that \u2026 ok, but not exciting \u2026</p>\n<p>However, the vintage (1993) has not yet excited me generally \u2026 rarely any wine did really \u201csing\u201d so far (yes, there were 2-3 wines) \u2026  from Village to Grand cru \u2026 usually a bit \u201cangular\u201d, tannins a bit \u201cdry\u201d, not really sweet and round \u2026</p>\n<p>(all very general)</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thanks for the info Gerhard<br>\nIf it was a LSG, it would indeed not be modest. Alas it is only a village wine. I can not find the lieut dit stated in the label.<br>\nThe wine was indeed a bit dry, but fresh. I have had several great 1.er Cru from 1993.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Claus,<br>\nyou are right, sorry, my mistake - I looked carelessly on the pic \u2026 and read LSG \u2026 <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/c/c5807a20e70dd93070f88bace4e4081a35b2a6aa.gif\" width=\"35\" height=\"45\" alt=\"pileon\" title=\"[pile-on.gif]\" class=\"animated\"></p>\n<p>However, it seemes to be a cuvee of<br>\nLes Saint-Julien / Les Plateaux -<br>\ntwo Village sites north and south close to the town \u2026 many Hospice-wines are cuv\u00e9es (also Hospice de Beaune), due to the donator - but it is quite unusual to name the exact lieu-dits if more than one \u2026</p>",
